prompt_text:
Write a clear and actionable {update_period} status update for the {project_name} project. The update should give stakeholders and team members a quick, honest snapshot of where things stand without requiring them to dig into details. Lead with a one-line overall status assessment (on track, at risk, or off track) before diving into specifics.

Summarize the following accomplishments from this period:
{accomplishments}

Outline the upcoming planned work:
{upcoming_work}

Call out any blockers or dependencies that need attention:
{blockers}

Format the update for easy scanning with bullet points and section headers. Highlight items that require action or decisions from others, and be transparent about risks rather than burying them. The goal is to build trust through consistent, honest communication that helps the broader team stay aligned and unblock each other proactively.
